            "answer_text": "They have what\u2019s called a back haul connection[1]. That connection allows each cell tower to connect to the carriers main network. In turn, the carrier\u2019s network connects to other networks and ultimately the Internet. Those back haul connections can be things like fiber optic cables or directional microwave antennas. Footnotes[1] Backhaul (telecommunications) - Wikipedia",
