                "href": "/profile/Scott-Helms-8"
            },
            "answer_text": "As Kevin Rome indicated, all base stations have to have back haul. That\u2019s true not just for the Internet connection, but to make phone calls. Towers and the base stations wouldn\u2019t be very useful if you could only communicate with other end points that were connected to the same tower as yours. If you think about the local LTE network as a LAN with the back haul connection acting as the WAN then you\u2019re in the right ball park. ",
